Package: EZscRNA
Title: Simple Convenience Functions for High-Level scRNA-Seq Analysis
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: person("Jared", "Andrews", email = "jared.andrews07@gmail.com", 
    role = c("aut", "cre"),
    comment = c(ORCID = "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0780-6248"))
Description: This package serves as a (hopefully) convenient wrapper for 
    EZ(-er) scRNA-seq analysis using best practices. It uses Seurat (v3+),
    sctransform, and slingshot (v3+) for most analysis steps. It provides a 
    number of high-level functions spanning QC/preprocessing, exploratory 
    data analysis, clustering, cell type inference using user-provided 
    reference data sets, pseudotime trajectories, and visualizations.
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0),
    Seurat (>= 3.0.0),
    sctransform (>= 0.2.0)
Imports: 
    dplyr,
    cowplot,
    ggplot2,
    foreach,
    doParallel,
    RColorBrewer
Suggests:
  scales
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
